[2] First number denotes discharge size.
    Second number denotes suction size.
    Third number denotes impeller size.

    THD - Threaded connection
[3] A - Speed
        None - 3450 RPM
        4    - 1725 RPM

[11] Models are named as [A]-NR3XL[B] where:
     [A] Indicates end connection diameter:
         12  – 1/2"
         34  – 3/4"
         1   – 1"
         114 – 1 1/4"
         112 – 1 1/2"
         2   – 2"
     [B] Indicates end connection type, which may be combined in any combination:
         None – Standard with single union FNPT connection
         C    - Single union FC (copper sweat) connection
         CPVC - Single union female CPVC tailpiece connection (3/4" & 1" only)   
         DM   - Double male meter thread connection (no tailpieces) (3/4" & 1" only)
         DMSS - DM with SS spring & seal cage (3/4" & 1" only)
         DU   - Double union FNPT connection (or used with C, CPVC, LU, PEX)
         HRSC - High Range with Seal Cage (1/2" - 1 1/4" only)
         LU   - Regular body, less union assembly (no tailpieces), FNPT X FNPT
         PEX  - Single union PEX tailpiece connection (3/4" & 1" only)
         P    - Tapped and plugged for gauge
         SC   - Sealed cage bell housing with stainless steel adjustment bolt, lock nut, and 
                spring
